    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat the reserved pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> <strong>& garlic </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add 2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and stir for 30 secs</p><p>Gradually add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[90ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong>, 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[90ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>grated cheese</strong>, then season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – these are your <strong>creamed leeks</strong></p>",
