      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the leeks are thickening, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>to a measuring jug with your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Marmite </strong>and <strong>onion marmalade</strong></p><p>Gradually stir in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[300ml] </span>of <strong>boiled water</strong>, then transfer to the <strong>microwave </strong>for 2 min, stirring halfway, or until the gravy has thickened –<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
